Returns a retry decorator for both async and sync functions.

Parameters:

  • exceptions ‚Äì an exception or a tuple of exceptions to catch. default: Exception.

  • tries ‚Äì the maximum number of attempts. default: -1 (infinite).

  • delay ‚Äì initial delay between attempts. default: 0.

  • max_delay ‚Äì the maximum value of delay. default: -1 (no limit).

  • backoff ‚Äì multiplier applied to delay between attempts. default: 1 (no backoff).

  • jitter ‚Äì extra seconds added to delay between attempts. default: 0. fixed if a number, random if a range tuple (min, max)

  • graceful ‚Äì whether to raise an exception if all attempts fail or return with None. default: False.

default(o)[source]#

Implement this method in a subclass such that it returns a serializable object for o, or calls the base implementation (to raise a TypeError).

For example, to support arbitrary iterators, you could implement default like this:

def default(self, o):
    try:
        iterable = iter(o)
    except TypeError:
        pass
    else:
        return list(iterable)
    # Let the base class default method raise the TypeError
    return super().default(o)
